          <div><span style="color:#b8a0ff">$</span> <span style="display:inline-block; width:8px; height:16px; background:#b8a0ff; animation:blink 1s step-end infinite;"></span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>@keyframes blink { 0%, 50% { opacity: 1; } 51%, 100% { opacity: 0; }}</style>

<!-- THE PROBLEM -->
<section class="lp-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Wall</p>
      <h2 class="heading-xl">Why Technical Leaders Plateau</h2>
      <p class="lead-center">It's not a skill gap. It's a translation gap.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lp-grid-3">
      <div class="lp-card">
        <h3>The Competence Trap</h3>
        <p>You're the smartest person in the room. So you solve the problems yourself. Your team escalates everything. You become the bottleneck.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-card">
        <h3>Influence Without Authority</h3>
        <p>Logic isn't persuasion. And no RFC will fix why the board or CFO doesn't see your recommendation the way you do.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-card">
        <h3>Delegation Feels Like Risk</h3>
        <p>When you delegate, quality might drop. When the breach hits, it's your name. So you hold on. The team doesn't grow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- BILINGUAL ADVANTAGE -->
<section class="lp-section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Unfair Advantage</p>
      <h2 class="heading-xl">A Coach Who Speaks Both Languages</h2>
      <p class="lead-center">Most coaches understand leadership but not your world. Most consultants understand your world but not leadership.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lp-creds">
      <div class="lp-chip">ICF PCC</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">CPCC (Co-Active)</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">CISA</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">CISM</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">CRISC</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">PMP</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">PMI-ACP</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">PSM III</div>
      <div class="lp-chip">Six Sigma MBB</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRANSFORMATION ARC -->
<section class="lp-section-dark">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Arc</p>
      <h2 class="heading-xl">From Technician to Strategic Leader</h2>
      <p class="lead-center">Four stages. Every technical leader passes through them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lp-grid-3" style="margin-top:56px;">
      <div class="lp-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
        <h3 style="color:white;">1. Expert</h3>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">Your technical depth is the value. The team relies on your knowledge. Promotions come from competence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
        <h3 style="color:white;">2. Manager</h3>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">You delegate tasks but not decisions. Everything flows through you. The bus factor is 1. This is where most plateau.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
        <h3 style="color:white;">3. Architect → Strategist</h3>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);">You design systems and decision rights. The team operates without you. Coaching gets you here.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

